x4freetext: -THERMAL NEUTRON CAPTURE IN 63-EU-151.-
.FR 2 REACTOR KARLSRUHE.
GRAPHITE SCATTERER IN THE TANGENTIAL THROUGH
HOLE OF THE FR 2 REACTOR. THERMAL NEUTRON BEAM.
.PURE 96.83 PER CENT ENRICHED EU-151 SAMPLE.
.THE LARGE CROSS-SECTION ELEMENTS CD,SM,GD
AND DY WERE LESS THAN 0.002, 0.04, 0.15 AND 0.01 PER
CENT, RESPECTIVELY.
.DIRECT DETECTION OF GAMMA SPECRA BY THE
KARLSRUHE GE(LI) ANTI-COMPTON SPECTROMETER. SEE
W.MICHAELIS ET AL., NUCL. PHYS. A143(1970)225.
KARLSRUHE GE(LI) ANTI-COMPTON SPECTROMETER,
CONSISTING OF A GE(LI)DIODE 5 CM3,
A PLASTIC SCINTILLATOR TYPE NE102A,(50 CM DIA)* 40 CM,
AND A NAI(TL) CRYSTAL (10.16 CM DIA) * 15.24 CM.
.THE ENERGY RESOLUTION INCLUDING LONG-TERM INSTABILITY
WAS 1.96 KEV FWHM FOR THE 841.57 KEV GAMMA-RAY FROM
THE EU-152M1 (EC) DECAY.
.THE RESPONSE FUNCTION OF THE SPECTROMETER WAS DETER-
MINED WITH A SET OF ABSOLUTELY CALIBRATED GAMMA-RAY
SOURCES.
.NORMALIZED TO A VALUE OF 4.58 FOR THE 841.57 KEV GAMMA
RAY FROM THE EU-152M1 EC DECAY. THIS VALUE WAS
CALCULATED FROM THE TOTAL RADIATIVE CAPTURE CROSS-
SECTION (8800 +- 100 B), THE CROSS-SECTION FOR PRO-
DUCTION OF THE 9.3 H ISOMERIC STATE (3100 +- 400 B)
AND THE GAMMA RAY INTENSITY I(841.57) = 13 +- 1 PER
CENT FOR EU-151M1 EC DECAY.  C.M.LEDERER ET AL., TABLE
OF ISOTOPES, 6TH ED.,  NEUTRON CROSS SECTION BNL-325,
2ND EDITION.
.THE ENERGY RESOLUTION WAS 1.96 KEV FWHM FOR 841.57 KEV
GAMMA.
.THE ERRORS FOR INTENSITIES INCLUDE UNCERTAINTIES FROM
THE COMPTON BACKGROUND, THE STATISTICS, THE FITTING
PROCEDURE AND THE SPECTROMETER RESPONSE FUNCTION.  IN
GENERAL, THE MAIN CONTRIBUTION IN THE ERRORS COMES
FROM THE DETERMINATION OF THE BACK GROUND UNDER THE
PEAKS.
